      "writtenOn": "2016-10-28T13:53:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In a past project, we had a way to write tests and have them compile, but indicate they are failing or flaky due to a known bug. Maybe something like:\nfunc FailingTest(t *testing.T, bug int) {\n  if !shouldRun(FAILING_TEST) {\n    t.Skipf(\"Skipping test due to http://skbug.com/%d\", bug)\n  }\n}\n\nThis can also be helpful for TDD.\n\nWith said past project, we also had a tool to identify tests tagged with bugs that had been closed, but I\u0027m not sure that\u0027s really necessary for infra.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 78,
        "startChar": 24,
        "endLine": 78,
        "endChar": 29
      },
